# Demo page conventions

## Structure

- `demo/index.html` — semantic sections only; no inline styles. Each mode gets
  a numbered `.block` with `aria-labelledby` pointing at its `<h2>`.
- `demo/demo.css` — all page chrome. Component appearance stays in Shadow DOM
  (`src/styles.ts`); do not style `.card` / shadow internals from the demo.
- `demo/main.ts` — wiring only (CMS endpoint, playground, resize readout,
  event logging). No DOM templating.

## Required UX affordances

- **Skip link** to `#main-content` as the first focusable element.
- **CMS status pill** (`#cms-status`, `role="status"`, `aria-live="polite"`)
  updated on `featurecards:ready` / `featurecards:error`.
- **Playground** (`#playground`) drives `#playground-instance` via CSS custom
  properties — not `#inline-instance` (those cards have fixed per-card themes).
- **Resize readout** (`#resize-readout`) fed by `ResizeObserver` on `#resizable`.
  Resize handle lives in CSS (`resize: horizontal`); show a corner affordance.

## Copy & content

- Section notes (`.block-note`) explain *why*, not just *what*. Use `<code>` for
  attributes, npm scripts, and adapter names.
- Light-DOM demo links use `data-eyebrow`, `data-description`, `data-theme`,
  and distinct `data-cta` labels.
- Meta `fc-cms-endpoint` points at production; dev defers to
  `VITE_FC_CMS_ENDPOINT` in `demo/main.ts`.

## CMS wiring

- Set `src` once — do not probe-fetch before the component fetches. On error,
  retry with `/fixtures/cards.json` and update the status pill to `fallback`.

## Do not

- Add framework CSS or component libraries to the demo.
- Hide loading/error states behind console-only logging.
- Break the five demo instances' card counts (3 + 3 + 3 + 2 playground + 2
  resizable) without updating e2e tests.
